Tony Okafor, Awka The Chairman of INNOSON Vehicle Manufacturing Company, Nnewi, Anambra State, Innocent Chukwuma, has described Niger Delta youths as highly talented and skilful. Chukwuma who had helped in training some youths in the area under a Federal Government arrangement, said the youths of the region assisted in the growth and development of his company. He said, “Some of the youths of the Niger Delta who we trained are very talented and skilful. “We trained and retained some of them and they are part of the success story of Innoson vehicle manufacturing company today.” He stated this on Sunday at a press conference in Nnewi, Anambra State He commended President Muhammadu Buhari for the patronage he had given to his company. He said the Buhari-led Federal Government had given INNOSON company the desired support and encouragement. He listed Enugu, Ebonyi, Ekiti, Imo, Kogi, Anambra, Gombe, and Bauchi states as well as the Nigeria military as those patronising INNOSON vehicles. While calling for more patronage, Chukwuma said the company had the vision and potential to make Nigeria a vehicle manufacturing destination in Africa. “I must equally say that some state governments like Ekiti, Imo, Enugu, Ebonyi, Kogi, Gombe, Anambra and Bauchi are giving us a great boost. Copyright PUNCH.
